{"article_id":"1BSfJ3uSDROqqBiS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court announced on Monday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that it will hear California v. Texas and United States House of Representatives v. Texas , two consolidated cases","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that represent an existential threat to Obamacare ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"and that were brought by a coalition of Republican-governed states .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"For the third time","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"since President Barack Obama signed the Affordable Care Act in 2010 ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"the justices will hear a lawsuit","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"seeking to eviscerate the legislation .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Texas turns on Congress ' s decision","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"to repeal Obamacare ' s individual mandate .","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"As originally enacted , the Affordable Care Act requires most Americans to either obtain health insurance","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"or pay higher taxes .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"The tax law","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"President Donald Trump signed in 2017","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"reduces the amount of that tax to zero .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Because the Supreme Court upheld the fully functional mandate as a valid exercise of Congress ' s power","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"to tax in 2012 ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"the Texas plaintiffs argue","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that the zeroed-out version of the mandate is unconstitutional","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"- how can something be a tax","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"if it raises no money whatsoever ?","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"They also claim","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"that the entire Affordable Care Act must fall","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"if the deactivated mandate is unconstitutional .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"The Republican legal arguments against Obamacare in this case are widely viewed as ridiculous , even by many lawyers and scholars","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"who spent much of the last decade","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"trying to convince the courts to repeal President Obama ' s signature achievement .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Jonathan Adler , a conservative law professor","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"- and a leading evangelist for an earlier lawsuit","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"seeking to undercut the Affordable Care Act","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"by reading a poorly drafted provision of the law","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"to cut off much of the act ' s funding -","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"labeled many of the red states ' arguments \" implausible , \" \" hard to justify , \" and \" surprisingly weak. \"","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"The Wall Street Journal ' s editorial board labeled this lawsuit the \" Texas Obamacare Blunder. \"","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Yuval Levin , a prominent conservative policy wonk , wrote in the National Review","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"that the Texas lawsuit \" doesn ' t even merit being called silly .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"It ' s ridiculous . \"","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"And yet , the lawsuit has received very favorable treatment from Republican federal judges .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Judge Reed O ' Connor , a former Republican Senate staffer turned district judge , ordered the whole Affordable Care Act repealed in its entirety .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Two Republican federal appeals court judges reached a somewhat more mild conclusion","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"- striking down a small portion of the law","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and then sending the case back down to O ' Connor","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"to reconsider","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"which other provisions should fall .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"But ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"while that holding creates more work for Judge O ' Connor ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"he remains likely to kill as much of the law","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"as he can .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"In addition to weighing the merits of the plaintiffs ' arguments ,","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"the Supreme Court will need to consider","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"whether any federal court has jurisdiction","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"to hear this case .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"As a general rule , no one is allowed to challenge a law in federal court","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"unless they can show","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"they were injured by that law .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Because the zeroed-out mandate does nothing ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"it ' s highly doubtful that anyone is allowed to challenge it .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"Assuming that President Trump does not get to replace any of the current justices ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"the Supreme Court is unlikely to agree with the lower-court judges","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"who ruled against Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Chief Justice John Roberts twice broke with his conservative colleagues in lawsuits","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"attacking Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"and Roberts is especially likely to reject the Texas plaintiffs ' legal arguments .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"But ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"so long as this lawsuit exists ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"it remains a threat to Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"And there is no guarantee","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"that the court ' s membership will not change .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"As noted above ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"the Affordable Care Act originally required most Americans to either carry insurance or pay higher taxes .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"The Supreme Court famously upheld this provision ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"known as the \" individual mandate , \"","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"as a valid exercise of Congress ' power","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"to levy taxes","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"in NFIB v. Sebelius","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"( 2012 ) .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Congressional Republicans spent much of 2017 debating various plans","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"to repeal Obamacare ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"but they ultimately did not have the votes for a broad repeal .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"They did , however , manage to repeal the individual mandate in the 2017 tax legislation .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"Though the United States Code still contains Obamacare ' s language","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"requiring individuals to pay a tax penalty","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"if they do not have insurance ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"the amount of that penalty is now zero dollars .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"The Texas plaintiffs claim","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"that this shell of a mandate is unconstitutional .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"The fully functional mandate was constitutional","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"because it is a tax ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"but a zero dollar tax is no tax at all .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"So the Texas plaintiffs argue","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"that it must be unconstitutional .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"That ' s not a frivolous argument ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"but so what ?","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"The zeroed mandate already does nothing .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"So who cares if a provision of the law","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"that literally does nothing at all","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"is constitutional or not ?","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"To achieve anything meaningful ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"the Texas plaintiffs don ' t just need to convince the courts","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that a nothingburger mandate is unconstitutional .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"They also have to get a majority of the justices to embrace two other arguments :","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"the claim","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"that the Texas plaintiffs may challenge a legal provision","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that does nothing","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"and the claim","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"that the entire Affordable Care Act must fall .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"That ,","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"as Levin wrote ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"is utterly ridiculous .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"By conventional standards , no federal court should be allowed to hear this case","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"Before anyone is allowed to challenge a law in federal court ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"they must show","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"that they ' ve been injured in some way by that law","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"- a requirement","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"known as \" standing. \"","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"That alone should be enough","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"to doom the Texas litigation .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"Because the plaintiffs challenge a provision","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"that does nothing at all ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"no one is injured by it .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"So no one has standing .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"The plaintiffs argue","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"they can get around this problem","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"by pointing to the way","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"Obamacare ' s language","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"laying out the individual mandate","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"is structured .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"The first subsection of that language says","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"that most individuals \" shall \" carry health insurance ;","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"the second says","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"that people","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"who don ' t buy insurance","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"pay a tax penalty ;","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"the third sets the amount of that penalty","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"- which , again , is now zero dollars .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"Although the penalty","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"for not buying insurance","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"is nothing ,","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"the plaintiffs claim","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"that individuals are still bound by the language","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"that they \" shall \" carry insurance","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"- and therefore are injured by a law","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"that commands them to do something","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"they don ' t want to do .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"The biggest problem with this argument is that it runs counter to the Supreme Court ' s decision in NFIB , the decision","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"upholding the fully functional individual mandate .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"As Chief Justice Roberts explained :","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Neither the Act nor any other law attaches negative legal consequences to not buying health insurance ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"beyond requiring a payment to the IRS .","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"The Government agrees with that reading ,","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"confirming","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"if someone chooses to pay rather than obtain health insurance ,","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"they have fully complied with the law .","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"Thus , the Supreme Court explicitly rejected the Texas plaintiffs ' argument","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"that they are bound by a command","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"to buy insurance .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"There are no \" negative legal consequences to not buying health insurance \"","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"except having to pay a tax penalty .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Anyone","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"who pays that penalty","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"has \" fully complied with the law. \"","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"And the amount of that penalty ,","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"in case this isn ' t already clear ,","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"is now zero dollars .","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"But let ' s assume , for a moment ,","depth":7},{"id":167,"text":"that these plaintiffs have the standing","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"to challenge a law","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"that does nothing .","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"Let ' s also assume","depth":7},{"id":171,"text":"that the ex-mandate is unconstitutional .","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"What then ?","depth":5},{"id":173,"text":"When a court strikes down one provision of a broader statute ,","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"it often must ask","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"whether other provisions of the statute must fall along with it .","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"This inquiry is called \" severability , \"","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"and it ' s typically a speculative inquiry .","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"Courts ask","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"which hypothetical law Congress would have enacted","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"if it had known","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"that a particular provision was invalid .","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"There ' s no need","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"to speculate in Texas , however ,","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"because Congress already answered this question .","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"Lawmakers spent most of 2017","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"debating how much of the Affordable Care Act to repeal .","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"Ultimately , they only had the votes","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"to repeal one provision , the individual mandate ,","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"while leaving the rest of the law intact .","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"So we know","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"that Congress would have enacted a law","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"that eliminated the individual mandate","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"and kept the rest of the law","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"because Congress enacted a law","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"that eliminated the individual mandate","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"and kept the rest of the law .","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"This conclusion is bolstered by the Supreme Court ' s decision in Murphy v. NCAA","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"( 2018 ) ,","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"which held","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"that courts should apply a very strong presumption","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"against striking additional provisions of a law","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"when one provision is declared unconstitutional .","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"\" In order for other ... provisions to fall , \"","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"Justice Samuel Alito wrote for the Court in Murphy ,","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"\" it must be ' evident that [ Congress ] would not have enacted those provisions","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"which are within its power , independently of [ those ]","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"which [ are ] not . ' \"","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"The question","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"facing the Supreme Court now ,","depth":8},{"id":210,"text":"in other words ,","depth":7},{"id":211,"text":"is whether the Court will apply its ordinary standing rules as well as the rule","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"it announced in Murphy ,","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"in a politically charged case","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"involving a law","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"that Republicans hate above all others .","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"Roberts has twice signaled","depth":5},{"id":217,"text":"that he is not willing to embrace dubious legal claims","depth":6},{"id":218,"text":"in order to undercut Obamacare ,","depth":6},{"id":219,"text":"so the Texas plaintiffs are unlikely to prevail .","depth":4},{"id":220,"text":"But","depth":4},{"id":221,"text":"if Trump gets to fill another Supreme Court seat ,","depth":5},{"id":222,"text":"all bets are off .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":445,"left":298,"right":444,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":246,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":232,"right":245,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":230,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":226,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":0,"right":225,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":1,"right":224,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":229,"left":227,"right":228,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":227,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":242,"right":244,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":236,"right":241,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":233,"right":235,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":235,"left":234,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":234,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":237,"right":240,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":237,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":238,"right":239,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":239,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":21,"right":243,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":243,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":269,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":